items.text: The eggs benedict (with spinach) for brunch/lunch or if you have a sweet tooth the very berry french toast.
Close every MON!!
This is a fancy restaurant in an old restored church--their prices are a little steep for dinner, but if you want to go there for lunch one day they have a pretty reasonable set menu!
The whole dining inside a chapel experience made this one of my favorite fine dining restaurants in Singapore. My set: Tuna Carpaccio, Salmon Roulade & Creme Brulee.

The former chapel turned restaurant-bar delivers solid classic European dishes replete with fancy cocktails. Try the mac & cheese (dressed with black truffle slices) or splurge on cote de boeuf for 2.
Lovely ambience with matching food standards
Must try their eggs benedict
Don't order the English breakfast/fry-up. Not worth the SGD24. The sausage was a nugget. The quiche was more worthwhile at SGD16.
Eggs benedict - Perfect poached eggs and a scrumptious hollandaise sc takes the cake.
First class service! Amazing & tasty foods! Ambience is wonderful. I'll surely come back to this place again.
Everything we had were delicious and the service was fabulous. Beautiful chapel to dine in 🍷
The eggs benedict is really good, though in general the place is a bit pricy overall.
Very average food. Very poor service. Heavily overated. One of my worst Singapore dining experiences. To be avoided
Amazing interior, remodeled old chapel. Ate the 5 course tasting menu. 2 courses were brilliant. 2 courses average, and 1 course was outright bad. Wine pairing for all courses was great.
This formerly dilapidated garrison church on Harding Road was said to be haunted by the ghost of a little boy who appeared near the entrance each day at around 4pm.
The Wagyu Carpaccio is sheer delight. Paper thin slices of Wagyu beef, balsamic pearls and truffle cream combine to make this one of the best appetizers I have ever eaten...
I read mixed reviews about this place but having tried the food here I must say we are impressed. The service was also great too! Love the high ceiling and outdoor garden...nice!!
This Alaskan king crab ravioli is lipsmackin' tasty and addictive. Love the texture of the garnish and crunch from the crab. The bisque is awesome too. Only thing is that the ravioli is too thick
Fine dining, with fine food and nice service.
36-hours Brandt Short Ribs. yums. The only disappoint: small portion.
Good view, yummy food
Gorgeous,awesome,luxury place with good cuisine &professional; staff!I'm going crazy for LobsterBisque-$38,Scallops-$28,CrepesSuzette-$20!Everything else insanely delicious,too!Average bill f2-$250
Worst service ever. It takes over 20 mins just to get a beer!
Nice ambience. Should try their molten laval dessert. Nice!!
The tuna carpaccio was lacking in flavour but the mushroom risotto was really good. The foie gras was sweet and lobster - succulent. Staff were warm and friendly but must say the lighting is too dim.
Place is hard 2 find if Yr driving in the nite. Low lights n it's signs is only showing 1 direction.Service setting looks classy but afew of the staff juz put or serve drinks without saying anything
Had a very memorable anniversary dinner with wife here. Church ambiance made it kinda romantic but food and service was average only. Good for special occasions.
Eat cote du beuf if you dare. Best hunk of meat tasted world wide
Really lovely pplace but best to make a reservation first as this place is really popular.
The tuna to start is good. Sea bass is done well and a good light option. Wine list is a little over priced and not a v.good selection.
Brunch here is very awesome...highly reccomended
So atasssssssssssss
Try the ricotta pancakes. Great presentation & pancake texture is amazing! :)
Wonderful place for baptism dinner! Waygu beef is v good! Service is attentive; dining in a chapel is memorable and significant.(3 Latin words: “Ego Te Baptizo”)
Go to White Rabbit and get yourself a blackforest mojito. Mmmm, you won't regret it!
Excellent services, plus they'll decorate a dessert plate & take a photo for your special someone's birthday if requested.
Housed in an old chapel in Singapore’s Demspey Hill, an area known as a local foodie haven, the White Rabbit serves European comfort food in a romantic setting.
Very awesome Wagyu Ribeye steak!
Try their eggs menu. The cabonara seems abit tasteless
Ambience was nice. Expected great things from this place but very dissapointed with the service- food came out slow, waiters mixing up orders and it wasnt even busy.
Tenderloin is soso , but the foie gras and truffle slice on top is great
Weekend brunch is awesome!
Souffle and their Eggs Benedict were cooked to my satisfaction. The chocolate sorbet carries a tinge of rocher's hazelnutty taste.
yummy lobster chowder!
The Wagyu beef is amazing.
Such beautiful bones, almost holy as you walk.I can see where the pulpit could have been before. In some other life. Darling ,perhaps you've walked down a similar isle with me waiting at the end.
Awesome weekend Brunch! :)
Tuna carpaccio w soy caviar and olive dust is so so delishious. Foie gras w cherry compote is ingenius and mémorable. Roast chicken w wild shrooms and truffle mash is equally fantastic.
Fine dining experience in a Chapel. They cook the Crêpes Suzette in front of you
Check out the interior of the restaurant. It's beautiful.
Warm spinach salad + mac and cheese + scallop linguine + baked Alaska: all pretty good!
Soufflé is gorgeous. Top notch service. Realised last minute that I lost my UOB cards which entitles to free coffee or tea. Service staff has the flexibility to serve it complimentary. Thanks v much.
Truffle overload on the menu, especially the sides. It's not necessary to put truffle on everything.
Nice beef carpaccio with truffles. Seabream was very good too
Service is not good even when the restaurants is rather empty. Cups are dirty!!!
Love the food here!
Grab a drink at the rabbit hole and see how deep it goes.
Cosy place for dinner, great service, and excellent food. Beef carpaccio was rather memorable. Garden out back a nice spot for post dinner drinks.
Pretty good eggs benedict here
Platter with duck breast is excellent. Lovely design. Expensive but that pays for the ambience and food
Really beautiful setting in a former cathedral. Overall great food. Truffle pasta was fantastic. Pork chops had a great apple smoked flavor.
Had the sole fish and oyster pasta, both were good. For dessert we had the Alaska, not bad too.
Chapel-themed restaurant with decent food. Attentive service and fairly romantic setting. Notably pretty impressive cocktails.
Love the setting. At lunch recently they recommended the foie gras or the crab salad. The crab pasta was better but had shells. Had the Pot-Au-Feu for the main, but this was disappointing in flavour.
love the eggs benedict
Awesome atmosphere even with the outdoor seats
One of my fav chill and pre party spot.dinner is awesome too. Book early for a good seat
Duck confit is still one of my favorites with toasted hazelnut salad and caramelized onions. The mac& cheese tho not the best is still good. Finish with a Valrhona chocolate tart & doppio espresso.
Try the crispy duck leg
Beef Tartare
truffle chicken for 2.  gin n tonics.
